                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1617: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Glasgow</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-20">November 20,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Your 57, 18th.<note n="78" xml:id="d239fn78">Not printed.</note> Government
                    unable at this time to dispatch another vessel to British Isles to evacuate
                    Americans due to refusal of German Government to assure safe passage. In view of
                    intent and purpose of neutrality law to prevent travel in combat areas and
                    increasing perils of travel therein, Department declines authorize travel in
                    such areas on vessels of any character at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
